snippet: George Reyes will be one of only a few of the Internet search giant’s top executives to have left since its founding in 1998.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, Aug. 28  Google said Tuesday that George Reyes, the company’s longtime chief financial officer, plans to retire. He will be one of only a few of the Internet search giant’s top executives to have left since its founding in 1998.

headline.main: Finance Chief of Google Plans His Retirement at 53
